headline: Target (TGT) Valuation Check After Mixed Quarter, CEO Transition, and $5 Billion Modernization Push
summary: Target (TGT) just posted a quarter that looked fine on the surface, with revenue roughly matching expectations, but a weaker EBITDA line reminded investors that the turnaround is still a work in progress. See our latest analysis for Target. The share price has been choppy, with a modestly positive 7 day share price return but a sharply negative year to date share price return. Multi year total shareholder returns also remain under pressure as investors weigh execution risks against these...
